		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=742"><span id=>Archer</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />9 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Archer&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I haven't been a druid for too long, but for the time I have been a druid I've figured that druids aren't all that much to brag about at the really early levels, basically all we have is snare (Which is great though) and some DD. So we're a weak nuker with heal, until we get to that crucial level which is *9*. At 9 we get our damage shield, a great DD, and our next hp buff. Not to mention our next heal! I'm writing this mainly to help those young druids (like me) get to this crucial level asap. My druid is only 4 days young but almost level 8. I made a human druid, and you will probably have to use human/half-elf and start in Surefall. (Unless you wanna do a lot of walking) Levels 1-4 are your basic hack up newbie stuff, and sell your haul. At level 5 you can buy the crucial of your next spells. After that you hit Blackburrow, the most awesome zone for someone your level, why? The Gnoll Fang quest. If you don't know then I suggest you look it up, it's the best quest in this level range. So basically I hacked up scrawnies and collected as many fangs as possible. So you get exp for killing scrawnies and the quest, double exp! I generally wait until I get 10+ fangs to do a turn in, at level 6, 10 fangs gave me about half a bar of exp, (Maybe because I'm human) and probably only took me a few hours to collect them. I hope this is helpful to anyone starting a new druid, after you hit 9 the fun begins and you're ready to solo the snake ledge/pit. Safe journies!</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />The Elusive "Archer"</td></td></tr><tr><td co